# UrduTranslator Skill

## Purpose
Translates technical English MDX content to high-quality Urdu while preserving technical terms, code blocks, mathematical notation, and all MDX formatting. Maintains educational accuracy and readability for Urdu-speaking learners of robotics and AI.

## Inputs

```yaml
english_content:
  type: string (MDX)
  description: "Complete English MDX chapter content to translate"
  required: true

target_audience:
  type: string
  enum: [students, professionals, general]
  description: "Target audience for tone and complexity"
  default: students
  required: false

preserve_terms:
  type: array<string>
  description: "Technical terms to keep in English (auto-includes ROS 2, URDF, Gazebo, etc.)"
  example: ["ROS 2", "URDF", "Gazebo", "Publisher", "Subscriber"]
  required: false

glossary:
  type: object
  description: "Custom English-Urdu terminology mappings"
  example:
    "Node": "نوڈ"
    "Topic": "موضوع"
  required: false
```

## Output

Urdu MDX translation with:
- All text converted to Urdu (اردو)
- Technical terms kept in English: ROS 2, URDF, Gazebo, NVIDIA Isaac, VLA, Python, C++, etc.
- All code blocks preserved exactly as-is (Python/C++ code unchanged)
- LaTeX math expressions preserved: `$...$` and `$$...$$`
- MDX component tags unchanged: `<CodeBlock>`, `<Quiz>`, `<Callout>`, `<Diagram>` etc.
- Headings translated: `## Learning Outcomes` → `## سیکھنے کے مقاصد`
- Links preserved: `[Text](url)` → `[اردو متن](url)`
- YAML frontmatter unchanged (id, title, sidebar_label in English for routing)
- List bullets and formatting preserved
- Comments in code blocks translated only if standalone; inline code comments left as-is

## Quality Standards

✅ **Mandatory**
- All non-code text is in proper Urdu (Unicode U+0600 to U+06FF)
- Technical/proper nouns preserved in English
- Code blocks completely unchanged (no translation of variable names, function calls)
- MDX syntax integrity maintained (all `<>` tags intact)
- Math expressions preserved
- Links functional
- YAML frontmatter unchanged

✅ **Recommended**
- Use standard Urdu terminology for common concepts (see Glossary section)
- Maintain tone consistency with original (educational, clear, accessible)
- Add transliteration in parentheses for complex terms if helpful: `نوڈ (Node)`
- Preserve learning flow and section emphasis from original
- Review by native Urdu speaker

## Preservation Rules

### Code Blocks (100% Preserved)
```
<CodeBlock language="python" title="example.py">
{`# This stays EXACTLY the same
import rospy
def listener():
    rospy.Subscriber('chatter', String, callback)
`}</CodeBlock>
```
Becomes:
```
<CodeBlock language="python" title="example.py">
{`# This stays EXACTLY the same
import rospy
def listener():
    rospy.Subscriber('chatter', String, callback)
`}</CodeBlock>
```

### Technical Headings
- `## Introduction to ROS 2` → `## ROS 2 کا تعارف`
- `### Publisher-Subscriber Pattern` → `### Publisher-Subscriber نمونہ`
- `#### QoS Settings` → `#### QoS ترتیبات`

### Glossary of Standard Terms
| English | Urdu | Notes |
|---------|------|-------|
| Node | نوڈ | Keep "Node" in code/technical context |
| Topic | موضوع | Publisher/Subscriber communication |
| Service | سروس | ROS 2 request-reply pattern |
| Message | پیغام | Data structure |
| Package | پیکج | ROS 2 code organization |
| Workspace | کام کی جگہ | Development environment |
| Robot | روبوٹ | Mechanical system |
| Sensor | سینسر | Input device |
| Actuator | ایکچویٹر | Output device |
| Simulation | نقالی | Virtual environment |
| Learning Outcome | سیکھنے کا مقصد | Educational goal |
| Key Takeaway | اہم نکتہ | Summary point |
| Quiz | سوالات کا مجموعہ | Assessment |

## Usage Examples

### Example 1: ROS 2 Topic Chapter Translation
```
Input:
  english_content: [Complete MDX chapter on ROS 2 Topics]
  target_audience: students
  preserve_terms: ["ROS 2", "Topic", "Publisher", "Subscriber", "Quality of Service"]

Output:
  urdu_content: اردو میں مکمل MDX فصل
  - تمام متن اردو میں
  - ROS 2, Publisher, Subscriber وغیرہ انگریزی میں رہے
  - تمام کوڈ بلاک بالکل ویسے ہی
  - تمام لنکس محفوظ
```

### Example 2: Advanced Simulation Chapter
```
Input:
  english_content: [Physics simulation chapter with equations and C++ code]
  target_audience: professionals
  glossary:
    "Dynamics": "حرکیات"
    "Contact": "رابطہ"
    "Grasp": "پکڑ"

Output:
  urdu_content: [High-quality Urdu translation with proper terminology]
```

## Limitations
- English-only source text (other languages not supported)
- Native Urdu speaker review recommended for technical accuracy
- Context-dependent terms may need glossary customization
- Regional Urdu variations (Pakistan vs. India) should be specified
- Translation quality depends on source content clarity

## Integration
Part of @Translator subagent workflow. Run after chapter finalization. Paired with human review for quality assurance. Supports bonus goal: multilingual educational content.

## Success Metrics
- 100% code block preservation (no changes)
- 95%+ valid Urdu text (Unicode correct, grammar sound)
- Zero broken MDX syntax
- All external links functional
- Glossary terms consistent across all chapters

